T1  - Historical Search in Human Relations
AU  - Whiting, Richard J.
Y1  - 1964/03/01
PY  - 1964
DA  - 1964/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255233
DO  - 10.5465/255233
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 45
EP  - 53
VL  - 7
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article explores the possibility of industrial human relations study in historical depth. A discussion is presented about the need for a new dimension or emphasis in order to integrate human relations theory into traditional management theory, which would allow the integration of human relations concepts and findings not only into the literature of management theory but also into the minds, actions and attitudes of managers. The author presents an overview of the developments and history of human relations study in the United States.
