TY  - JOUR
T1  - TFX—A Case in Policy Level Decision-Making
AU  - Bryan, Stanley E.
Y1  - 1964/03/01
PY  - 1964
DA  - 1964/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255234
DO  - 10.5465/255234
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 54
EP  - 70
VL  - 7
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a case study of policy level decision-making. In November 1962, the U.S. Secretary of Defense awarded the TFX development contract to General Dynamics Corp. A discussion is presented about the decision-making process and standard source selection procedure followed by the United States Armed Forces. The decision was made immediately after a unanimous recommendation from top military officers, through a standard source selection procedure, to award the contract to Boeing Airplane Co.
