TY  - JOUR
T1  - Project Management Recognizes R&D Performance
AU  - Roman, Daniel D.
Y1  - 1964/03/01
PY  - 1964
DA  - 1964/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255229
DO  - 10.5465/255229
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 7
EP  - 20
VL  - 7
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article explores issues on the measurement of the productivity and performance of professional scientific personnel in the U.S. Various industries in the country have been actively seeking a usable method of determining the productivity of professional scientific personnel. Techniques have been developed and used successfully in measuring the performance of workers in terms of physical units of product, yet there has been no comparable methods for determining the productivity and contribution of professionals engaged in mentally creative work. A discussion is presented about the importance of scientific development in the United States.
